      {
        "index": 1,
        "gloss": "setting off the night before one normally would have departed, travelling in a different direction, spending the night there, and leaving for one's destination in the morning (done to avoid travelling in an unlucky direction; a common practice during the Heian period)",
        "register": "standard",
        "nuance": null,
